      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to go past GEORGARONI (2) who is a lightly raced galloper in great form including back to back wins. Building a strong record this journey and at the course and distance. Drops in weight with the claim and led throughout last time so the small field suits. Should be the one to beat. ZEWINNA (3) just missed here two back then tackled open class over 1420m latest. Better suited here and gets chance to atone. HURRICANE KETUT (4) led and placed two back then scored over 1400m latest. Is already a three time winner this trip though and another aided by the small field. Will give a big sight. NICCO THE GREEK (1) is a handy type well placed this class and has another try at the mile. Was unplaced earlier in career only other attempt. Has been racing in open class lately so well placed back in grade. SKY LAND (6) is close to a win and gets chance to break through.",
